<br>
As an Alaskan, the need to defend oneself has more than one aspect. Consider the notion that there are more threats to oneself than humans in the Last Frontier. Bears. Angry Mama Moose. Rabid Mosquitoes add to the Peril Factor.<br>
<br>
Sure, you can carry that 16 oz bottle of Pepper Spray with you into the Great Outdoors with a feeling of being protected or having a Way Out, but when The Bears use it as seasoning, you know you have a Serious Problem on your hands. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Note to the readership: Bears in Alaska LIKE pepper spray. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
So, you either carry a gun, or carry pepper spray or nothing at all. You can try talking your way out of getting et to a bear, but bears don’t speak English. Or you can hose yourself down in that Pepper Spray to make the dining experience more pleasant for the bear. Or you can cycle the hammer back, knowing full well that the bear will have a Really Hard Time Eating You after you just put his anus into orbit around Mars.<br>
<br>
Take my guns away, and I can’t defend myself in the wilderness.<br>
<br>
I live in a really nice BIG house out in the middle of nowhere. It has a Great Big Loot Me Rob Me air about it. My neighbors can’t see me, and I can’t see them, so to a burglar, my house is open season.<br>
<br>
My house has been open season 2 times a year for the last 4 years. I would LOVE to be not allergic to dogs, since a good dog is far better than anything electronic you can put into your house. A good dog is miles better than the best gun. <br>
<br>
I won’t go into details or pith on any further. All I know is that the same laws that made drugs illegal will do no more to safeguard ME by making GUNS illegal. Heroine, cocaine, and crack are no less prevalent today than they were when they were outlawed, and yet, I am lead to believe that outlawing guns will make my community and MY life more secure by simple virtue that a law can and will rescue us all from the sins of mankind.<br>
<br>
By removing the ability of a populace to defend itself, you render that same populace unable to defend themselves in time of great need against a greater foe.<br>
<br>
Which is why we have the right to keep and bear arms.<br>
<br>
