Actually, a few years ago, a letter was written to a politician by an inmate in some prison (sorry I don't remember the details anymore) saying basically &quot;The only thing keeping me out of your house is the fact that you MAY have a gun in your bedroom dresser drawer.&quot;   Criminals don't want to get killed any more than anyone else does.  If a criminal breaks into your house in the middle of the night, with or without a gun, if you can wake up, you have a lot of advantages.  You know the house, even in the dark.<br>
<br>
As to outlawing guns, or taking the guns away.. does anyone actually think those laws would apply to the criminals (the people who would use guns to hurt innocent people) in the first place?  &quot;If guns are outlawed, only outlaws will have guns!&quot; -- it's kind of a cliche, but it's absolutely true.<br>
<br>
As for maintaining an armed militia to protect ourselves from a tyrannical government... well, I guess that argument has its valid points.  Hitler and Stalin were both big on gun control, and you know what happened there.  I don't see America becoming similarly tyrannical, but I imagine the mid-30's Germans didn't think they'd be embroiled in a holocaust, either.  And once they surrendered their guns to their government, there wasn't a lot they could do to stop Hitler's madness.<br>
